SUMMARY:Deadline: Copyright Agency Cultural Fund: Fellowship for Non-Fictio
 n Writing 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Copyright Agency Cultural Fund's Fellowship for Non-Fiction
  Writing awards AUD 80\,000 to one mid-career or established Australian au
 thor to research and write a substantial new work of literary non-fiction.
  Eligible forms include memoir\, biography\, history\, criticism\, arts an
 d science writing\, and environmental and political writing. ELIGIBILITY: 
 mid-career or established Australian authors with a demonstrated publicati
 on record and publisher interest in the proposed work\; Australian residen
 ts only. APPLICATIONS open 20 April 2026 and close 17 August 2026\, 1:00pm
  AEST. Apply via the Cultural Fund fellowship page.\n\nOrganisation: Copyr
 ight Agency (Cultural Fund)\nLocation: Australia\; Australian authors only
 .\nAward: AUD 80\,000 (one fellowship). No application fee.\nDuration: Fel
 lowship to research and write a new work\n\nMore: https://www.copyright.co
 m.au/culturalfund/fellowship/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_me
 dium=referral
URL:https://www.copyright.com.au/culturalfund/fellowship/?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Australia\; Australian authors only.
END:VEVENT
